reviews_data.review_text: Cool brewery/restaurant with nice brunch and coffee menu. Had a long layover in CLT and spent a few hours here. Friendly staff, good vibe.

The beer is great here but the service is so so bad. They are not attentive at all. Especially if you get food or would like anything else besides one beer. The employees behind the bar seem miserable and like they are inconvenienced by being there. As a customer, you need to initiate the conversation or what you’d like. Such a shame, that place has potential.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Alec, for taking the time to let us know about your experience. We try very hard to give every guest a great experience and it seems we missed the mark, and for that we apologize. We will use this to help teach our team. If you have any other specific feedback, please let me know at rrivera@thesuffolkpunch.com. Thank you.

reviews_data.review_text: LOVE their coffee and breakfast! Customer service is also immaculate. Shout out to Kelly and April, morning crew - they are so personable and are the reason I keep coming back
Great location with great food and awesome service! Celebrated a birthday for brunch here with no reservation and everything was perfect.
Food was delicious but there were dogs on the table where people eat. That is unsanitary. Will not be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Debra,
Thanks for visiting us and apologies for the dogs (& owners).  You are right about that.  We love our furry friends, but also have posted signs that dogs are not allowed on tables.  When we see it we do ask the owners to remove the dog, and we sanitize between customers.  We hope you'll give us another shot.

reviews_data.review_text: Great beer and food. Our server, Maddie, was AMAZING!! Will come back just for her personality and service!!
The best brunch and beer around.  Thank you Maddie for your fabulous service. We will be back!

I would’ve rated higher stars if they would pick up the phone. I have been calling multiple morning for the last couple of days and no one answers the phone.  all I want to know is if they still have their regular breakfast menu because they’ve got some contradicting information on their website
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi KM E,  Apologies for not answering!  You are correct, we are having issues with our phones currently, but they are in process of being fixed this week.  At South End we do a limited biscuit menu from 10-11am weekdays, and a full brunch menu from 10-2pm on Saturday and Sunday.  Our South Park location has a limited weekday breakfast menu from 8-11am, and full brunch from 10-2pm on Saturday and Sunday as well.  I hope this answers your question and I hope you will reconsider the one star review.  If you need more information, please reach out to us at info.southend@suffolkpunchbrewing.com

reviews_data.review_text: Brunch here was amazing. Food, atmosphere, and service were all on point.
Love coming to this location. The food and drinks are always great! Maddie was my server and she was super attentive and friendly. Would definitely recommend this brewery to anyone

I had came to Suffolk for margarita fest, and it was so packed!! But Maddie, who was running drinks out in this heat brought them quick, and was on top of it. Will be returning for how quick and easy the service was!!
Half Price shareables was great! Maddie even better! Highly recommend.

Great atmosphere! Huge variety of beers and cocktails ! AND … Maddie made our trip in even better. She was wonderful and sooooo friendly ! Thanks for the suggestions and outstanding service ! We will be back !

Amazing $3 lager on Thursdays!! Maddie was our server and she was absolutely amazing and so sweet! The interiors are so cute and the location is perfect!

First time impression was a thumbs down. Service was terrible, meaning that the bar staff ignored us most of the time and was only focused on the other end of the bar. Food was terrible and blah...won't be here again.

Hi Debbie,

reviews_data.review_text: while friendly, the service - specifically our server and the manager(s) walking around - was notably inattentive. my order was messed up, and it wasn’t until my table was well into their meals that we were able to get the waiter’s attention and return it (~15 minutes) as he did not check on us after it was served by other staff. it was also not comped/discounted, and i could only see after having already paid because i didn’t get a receipt. furthermore, as we finished waters and beers, we were not offered/asked about additional rounds and were only given more water upon asking whoever we could grab. this was interesting given we watched our server tend to surrounding tables regularly. the food and beer were good, though our experience could have been made better if we had been made to feel taken care of.

ANNE with Offline - This was a wonderful experience. I had the burrarita flatbread and my friend had the chicken Sammie. Both were so flavorful, perfectly cooked and quick service. The chicken was crispy topped with softest lightly toasted bread😋. They have a variety of mocktails for those who still want a fun drink without the alcohol.
The best coffee on the rail-trail! I always stop by to get Kelly’s teddy graham iced latte- the service is always fast & friendly as well.

Have enjoyed many beers out on the patio on a nice day. Stopped by on a weekday this time on a 95 degree day so got a table inside. Nachos and flatbread were both excellent. Jawripper is so damn good if you like smoothie sours. Service inside was not great, I prefer the QR ordering system outside, but overall enjoyed our weekday visit.

Today was a "day" at work so I needed to get out and have a beer. And after driving around South End behind stupid Charlotte drivers, I definitely needed a beer. Suffolk Punch isn't at all hard to find, right off South Tryon and they have a dedicated parking lot. So that's just awesome.

We seated ourselves at the table and Erin came by to take our drink order. A mocktail for Mrs. K. and a pilsner for me and when she returned with the drinks, we ordered a "flatbread" that really is a pizza.

It did take a bit considering the restaurant was almost empty but it was worth it. Burrata and cherry tomatoes and a balsamic drizzle. Absolutely delicious and reasonably priced.

We were here for at least an hour and I feel a whole bunch of destressed. Will need to return as their Monday night special is half off on burgers!

I love coming to Suffolk punch! It’s a great vibe. Great spot to come for lunch or grab a coffee in the morning. Love that you can scan a Toast QR code and order food & drinks for the table and pay your tab on your phone! They’ve got good specials on food & drinks and rotate their cocktail & beer menu so there’s always something new to try.
This review was made in connection with a Toast promotion.

Fantastic brewery and restaurant! This was our first time in Charlotte, and we wanted a spot with good beer, good food, and a lot of options. We weren't sure of everyone's dietary restrictions, so this seemed like a good choice so folks could have veggie, gluten-free, and non-alcoholic options if needed. I'm so glad we chose Suffolk Punch! All of the food was delicious, and the beer was pretty darn good as well. Plus, the atmosphere was delightful. 10/10, would recommend.

What do you want a brewery to be? This place has it all (other than being a dive). Good food, good beers, lots of seating options (inside, covered patio, outdoors) and lots of TVs to watch for games. Solid place!

This place is a really nice spot if you want to go for brunch + breakfast. I went on a Sunday and the outside patio was packed, so expect maybe to wait for a table if the weather is nice outside otherwise inside is usually pretty open.

My friends and I got the Big Bun Cinnamon roll and it was really good. I think if I really had to nit pick I would have wanted it to be more warmed up/ hot and then I think it would have made it taste even better. It was just barely warm/ at room temperature, but still tasted good nonetheless.

We also got their seasonal Cinnamon Toast Crunch cappuccino and their classic chicken biscuits. The chicken was season very well and the gravy was really tasty. The biscuit itself is different so I can see some people either not liking it as much or really love it.

Overall, everything tasted good and the waiters and staff were really nice and the overall restaurant had a nice atmosphere. Their parking lot is really small btw so you will need to plan maybe ahead to find some parking near by. I’d come back here again a solid 7.5/10. 👍

reviews_data.review_text:
Our go-to neighborhood haunt! Suffolk Punch has been a favorite of ours since it opened in 2017. It's conveniently located near our home and directly on the light rail, making it easy for anyone exploring Charlotte. They offer great upscale bar bites, weekly specials (like half-priced salads on Wednesdays), breakfast, a coffee bar, and in-house brewery options. The ambiance is consistently good and changes throughout the day, making it a perfect spot for remote work in the morning and a post-work drink in the evening.

Suffolk offers a refreshing atmosphere with a diverse crowd and a consistent, friendly staff who know us well. It's within walking or a quick driving distance of several other breweries, ideal for a brewery crawl, and has direct light rail access from the outdoor space. We visit with or without our kids for casual hangs and have had many business lunches here (and no, it doesn't feel like a playground like some breweries in CLT do). The back patio is very dog-friendly, great for people-watching, and the industrial warehouse space is beautifully decorated with hanging plants and a moody interior.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the love!  We appreciate your support over the years!

On my last visit, my sister and I ordered several plates to share - the Local Queen City Pretzel, the Warm Street Corn Dip, and the Strawberry Fields Salad. Everything was 10/10.

My Spicy Berry Margarita was delicious and refreshing. I was pleased to see they offered a mocktail option, which my sister ordered and said was awesome. We sat on the patio, which was the perfect spot to enjoy a sunny Sunday afternoon.

*UPDATE* Visited for brunch for the first time and was once again impressed! The chicken biscuit was amazing. I got it with a side salad, which was the perfect balance.

I’m a fan for life!

This review was made in connection with a Toast promotion.

Fantastic brewery and restaurant! This was our first time in Charlotte, and we wanted a spot with good beer, good food, and a lot of options. We weren't sure of everyone's dietary restrictions, so this seemed like a good choice so folks could have veggie, gluten-free, and non-alcoholic options if needed. I'm so glad we chose Suffolk Punch! All of the food was delicious, and the beer was pretty darn good as well. Plus, the atmosphere was delightful. 10/10, would recommend.

What do you want a brewery to be? This place has it all (other than being a dive). Good food, good beers, lots of seating options (inside, covered patio, outdoors) and lots of TVs to watch for games. Solid place!

This place is a really nice spot if you want to go for brunch + breakfast. I went on a Sunday and the outside patio was packed, so expect maybe to wait for a table if the weather is nice outside otherwise inside is usually pretty open.

Our go-to neighborhood haunt! Suffolk Punch has been a favorite of ours since it opened in 2017. It's conveniently located near our home and directly on the light rail, making it easy for anyone exploring Charlotte. They offer great upscale bar bites, weekly specials (like half-priced salads on Wednesdays), breakfast, a coffee bar, and in-house brewery options. The ambiance is consistently good and changes throughout the day, making it a perfect spot for remote work in the morning and a post-work drink in the evening.

Suffolk offers a refreshing atmosphere with a diverse crowd and a consistent, friendly staff who know us well. It's within walking or a quick driving distance of several other breweries, ideal for a brewery crawl, and has direct light rail access from the outdoor space. We visit with or without our kids for casual hangs and have had many business lunches here (and no, it doesn't feel like a playground like some breweries in CLT do). The back patio is very dog-friendly, great for people-watching, and the industrial warehouse space is beautifully decorated with hanging plants and a moody interior.
